@node 1 " BBS_LiST GUiDE v3.2 [c] 1997 Glen Martin    [Page 1 of 7] "
@prev main
@next 2



                   @{"            Description!            " link 1}

 In brief, BBS_LiST is simply a MAXs Door that displays the Oz BBS Listings.
 Also allows you to download the Oz BBS Listings archive, etc.

 This MAXs Door is only suitable for Ozzie MAXs SysOps ...

@endnode
@node 2 " BBS_LiST GUiDE v3.2 [c] 1997 Glen Martin    [Page 2 of 7] "
@prev 1
@next 3



                   @{"            Installation            " link 2}

 Very simple indeed, Unpack the BBS_LiST archive into your Doors directory.

@endnode
@node 3 " BBS_LiST GUiDE v3.2 [c] 1997 Glen Martin    [Page 3 of 7] "
@prev 2
@next 4



                   @{"            Instructions            " link 3}

 Grab the latest/current copy of the Australian BBS Listings archive. The
 copy of lists included are from Jan97 (BBS9701.LZH). In the archive you
 are too use the archive BBSDALL.LZH and BBSFALL.LZH. With each new version
 of the Listings you are to unpack the #?.TXT files from BBSDALL.LZH and
 BBSFALL.LZH into the directory called LiSTS within the directory BBS_LiST.
 Also place the copy of BBSDALL.LZH and BBSFALL.LZH in the LiSTS dir, as
 well. In the LiSTS dir there should be a total of 20 files; 18 #?.TXT
 files, and the BBSDALL.LZH and BBSFALL.LZH archives.

 The Door to run in MAXs (Function 34) is BBS_LiST.exe, and the menu to be
 displayed is called BBS_LiST.menu. Both these files reside in the main dir
 called BBS_LiST. The file BBS_LiST.heading is shown before the BBS lists.
 Just set it all up as it is, when you unpack it into your Doors dir ...

 You may alter watever to suit your BBS, etc!?

@endnode
